4.2.4.3.2.6.1	Summary of evidence and recommendations for other treatments for uncomplicated stress 
urinary incontinence

Implantation of an artificial sphincter can improve or cure incontinence in women with uncomplicated 
SUI.
Implantation of the adjustable compression therapy (ACT®) device may improve uncomplicated SUI.

Complications, mechanical failure and device explantation often occur with both the artificial sphincter 
and ACT©.
